In [126]:
def plot_confusion_matrix(conf_matrix, title):
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))  # Set the figure size
    sns.heatmap(conf_matrix, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues', cbar=False,
                xticklabels=['Not Converted', 'Converted'],  # Modify these labels based on your classes
                yticklabels=['Not Converted', 'Converted'])
    plt.title(title)
    plt.xlabel('Predicted')
    plt.ylabel('Actual')
    plt.show()

Actionable Insights and Recommendations¶

In [135]:
def evaluate_model(y_true, y_pred, model_name):
    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_true, y_pred)
    conf_matrix = confusion_matrix(y_true, y_pred)
    class_report = classification_report(y_true, y_pred)

    print(f"Accuracy of {model_name}: {accuracy:.2f}")
    print("\nConfusion Matrix:\n", conf_matrix)
    print("\nClassification Report:\n", class_report)

    return accuracy, conf_matrix

import pandas as pd
import joblib

def get_user_input():
    print("Please provide the following details for the lead:")
    def validate_input(prompt, valid_options=None, is_int=False, is_float=False):
        while True:
            user_input = input(prompt).strip()
            if is_int:
                try:
                    user_input = int(user_input)
                    return user_input
                except ValueError:
                    print("Please enter a valid number!")
                    continue
            elif is_float:
                try:
                    user_input = float(user_input)
                    return user_input
                except ValueError:
                    print("Please enter a valid decimal number!")
                    continue
            if valid_options:
                if user_input.lower() not in [option.lower() for option in valid_options]:
                    print("Enter proper input!")
                    continue
            return user_input
